definitions.definition: One at all ; at least one; at least one kind of; some; a positive quantity of.
examples: Do you think there's any point to/in trying to explain?
It won't do you any good .
"Give me your pen." — "I don't have any pen."
labels: chiefly in the negative or interrogative
chiefly with plural or uncountable nouns
definitions.label_groups: chiefly in the negative or interrogative , chiefly with plural or uncountable nouns

definitions.definition: A/an, each or some, no matter its/their identity or nature.
examples: Please bring some plates — any plates will do.
I'll drink any whiskey you've got.

definitions.definition: An unspecified but imminent (second, minute, day etc.).
examples: I expect the phone to ring at any moment.

main_definition: ( chiefly in the negative or interrogative , chiefly with plural or uncountable nouns ) One at all ; at least one; at least one kind of; some; a positive quantity of.
secondary_definitions: A/an, each or some, no matter its/their identity or nature.
( with time designations ) An unspecified but imminent (second, minute, day etc.).
